        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thanks for looking at this!\r\n> If #23581 were addressed then it would be easy to get the tabpage from `ev.win` :\r\n> \r\n> ```\r\n> local tabnr = vim.fn.win_id2tabwin(ev.win)[1]\r\n> ```\r\nEven if we had either the window number or the window id in the callback, I still don't think there would be a way to get the tabpage id since the tabpage doesn't exist by the time the autocommand is executed. `vim.fn.win_id2tabwin` returns the tab number which is already provided in `ev.file` (`<afile>`). ",
