        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Even if we had either the window number or the window id in the callback, I still don't think there would be a way to get the tabpage id since the tabpage doesn't exist by the time the autocommand is executed. \r\n\r\nOh right, thanks for calling that out. In that case it seems like `.tab` should be part of the `:help event-args` (`ev.tab` as opposed to `ev.data.tab`), i.e. we should promote this to a more standard field. \r\n\r\nAre you up for looking into that? It doesn't need to work for all events, but at least getting a routine in place would be worthwhile.\r\n",
            "created_at": "2026-04-26T10:15:48Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38537#issuecomment-4321799702",
