        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Update:\r\nI learned the `TabClosedPre` autcocommand was recently added (it was added four months ago in Neovim, 14 months ago in Vim) and could be used to solve the problem of learning when a tab is closed except for the fact that it doesn't provide the tab page number or tab id. However I noticed it does set the current tab page to the one being closed for the duration of the autocommand, so `tabpagenr('#')` returns the tab page number of the tab page being closed. I'm not sure if that's a bug though, since it isn't documented, so I'll check with Vim where it was added to see if it is. If it is a bug, it would be easy to add the tabnr as arguments like with `TabClosed`, and I'm surprised it isn't already, but in any case seems like this should be submitted to vim first.\r\n\r\nSidenote I also looked into passing the tabid as a parameter, but if ideally we'd always provide the window id then tab id is redundantt except for in `TabClosed`; although, since `TabClosedPre` solves this use case, currently I don't see a benefit to also providing tab id.",
